<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id6b689585-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e" identifier="/us/usc/t33/s702l"><num value="702l">§ 702l.</num><heading> Repeal of inconsistent laws</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">All laws or parts of laws inconsistent with sections 702a, 702b to 702d, 702e to 702g, 702h, 702i, 702j, and 702k of this title, are repealed.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id6b689586-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e">(<ref href="/us/act/1928-05-15/ch569/s12">May 15, 1928, ch. 569, § 12</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/45/539">45 Stat. 539</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
